caption: I always go pad Thai, and I usually like any pad Thai I have. Usually it’s “good” because you can’t go too wrong. But this pad Thai is delicious! This was my first time having Penny’s and I highly recommend! Something about the sauce or the veggies they use that makes it so tasty.
Absolutely the best thai food I've ever had....

I had not been in a long time. I was around when they first started opening spots. I was so happy to see the original one on Clark open. GREAT I will be going back often again. Love the amount of food for the price, and its sooooo 😋 delicious!!
The chicken pad thai is the best! Very generous with their portions, always have left overs.
Excellent take out, especially the hot pepper noodles 👌
Excellent food
Amazing good food and good prices
Penny's had been one of my favorite for over 20 years and the food is still amazing! Love it, love it, love this place, can you tell!
Great dining experience. Crazy noodle is delicious.
Best Thai fried rice I've had in Chicago
Great flavors, great variety, very nice staff.
Great food

Amazing food! I had the Pad We Eu and the egg noodles with BBQ pork. Both were amazing and reminded me of my travels in Asia. There staff was very friendly/welcoming and the seating space and kitchen looked immaculate and clean. Overall 10/10 and I will be orderig a lot more noodles in the near future.

So happy it’s Penny’s Noodles again! Had changed owners/name for a while. Just moved into the neighborhood and saw it was Penny’s again! My favorite place for Lad Nar w extra crispy noodles!! I always order it w along with other dishes.
I love their food. Glad they reopened
Love the hot pepper noddles, halve crunchi halve soft just amazing
Delicious food
Everything is always amazing.
Been going here forever. Food is consistently excellent.
Menu limited from previous visits & food didn't taste up to par. What's going on?!
So glad they are back! Same recipes taste great, same friendly staff, original location! My go-to Thai.

They do a really good job of offering leaner versions of some very rich dishes, and they offer a nice variety for a low price. The beef noodle soup is great, lean cuts of beef and a clear aromatic broth without much fat to speak of.
Always great. Customers for over 25 years.

When they closed in early 2019 for a while I cried. Then they reopened in the spot on Sheffield that they used to occupy so many years ago. Super fresh food. Portions are acceptable, sometimes on the smaller side but the taste has no rival. I would eat here 3 times a week if it were closer to home.

I think we will often go over there! The chicken satay was delicious as well the gyoza. Forget to take pic for starters but we have the Tonkatsu ramen that was delicious, not too salty and the soft egg so good!!
Tastier than the other two locations.

Always a favorite.  The only Thai restaurant (that I'm aware of) that serves Lard Nar with crispy, wide rice noodles (emphasis on crispy). Delicious! Only 11 two-top tables and a an additional 5 seats at a service bar, but service is quick.
Great food with affordable prices. I have not been unsatisfied with any item ordered. Highly recommend.

This place is soooooo delicious! This is my absolute favorite Thai restaurant in Chicago. Portion size is perfect, and service is friendly! There are so many dishes on the menu that I love! Below is the chicken noodle soup & Thai fried rice (so so good!).
Without exaggeration, I could eat nothing but their Thai ravioli and lad nar for dinner for the rest of my life and be perfectly happy.
One of my long time favorite places to get good Thai food.
Quick yummy bite for a reasonable price. Good service and easy to access by train. Friendly staff.
Delicious and big portions. I had the beef noodle soup, 10/10
Penny's Noodles holds a spot in my heart. Really delicious food. I recommend the vegetarian bowl or the pad thai.
The best Pad Thai in Chicago.
My favorite Thai restaurant in the city is back!! Pad se ew is my go to dish (sweet sauce with zero spice.) Quick, friendly service.
Food was delicious. Big portions, pretty cheap. It’s a small place, definitely better for takeout. Service was nothing special.
20 years ago this place was a regular part of my life... Maybe there's new ownership now or something, but it's complete sh_t.  Inconsistent and, sadly, just not very good food anymore.
Good food,  small, personable, friendly will visit again soon!

Good portions. Service was average. Prices good. Food was above average quality, but I just didnt enjoy. Thai fried rice was just too spicy for me but it was good. Wanton soup was not my taste either having a pork broth base...but my friend enjoyed it. I probably won't be back, but if I do will order different things.
We love Penny's!

This place was my go-to for 3 years when I lived on the same block and it was “Paul’s”. I was very excited to go back when the restaurant reopened under Penny’s! Paul’s had the best pad Thai I’ve ever eaten and I was hoping it was the same. To my surprise it tasted the exact same and was made with just slightly thinner noodles. I also ordered the crab rangoons, which we unfortunately had to send back because they were still cold in the center out of the fryer. The staff was very accommodating and brought us another order which was cooked perfectly! My friend got the Spicy Pepper Noodles (formerly Drunken Noodles which I have ordered many times before) and the noodles were squishy and over done but the dish tasted great. Overall great customer service and yummy food, but they need to work on consistency - which I’m sure will come with time.
Open kitchen very clean fresh and tasty food at reasonable prices.
Amazing,  inexpensive food with great hospitality!
This is my go-to noodle and ramen place. I typically get it delivered or pick it up, but the restaurant itself is cozy and can make for a really cute date night. Love it here.
Nothing special Chinese food.  BYOB
Great to see this dining institution back in its original location. The food has been so consistent for the past 25 plus years it's uncanny and  the service is great!
Friends took me here last night. NEW FAVORITE THAI PLACE. Noodles were delicious, chicken was FRESH. Def coming back <3
I've been here for many years with the family and the food is damn good, it's phenomenal. Service is excellent and the seating interior is nice and cozy. Love this place.
Great food and generous portions. I recommend the Thai Fried Rice or the Beef soup!
Quality food just as it has been over the many years. And at a great value.
Delicious comfort food, comfortably priced.

Hands down my fav Thai of the city. Been hauling myself to wicker but so happy to have you back in Wrigley! The food is always fresh, servers are always attentive and quick, and the portions are HUGE. Never a disappointment coming here! Friendliest staff in the city!
Great food and quick and excellent service. Glad Penny's is back
Best food Excellent service

BEST THAI AROUND I love Pennys! Always consistent, amazing flavor, and FRESH VEGGIES. I know its not what people come for but I appreciate the fact that they have sides and addition options of broccoli, watercress, chinese greens, and more. The BEST HIT tasty entrees, soups, appetizers, are still here after years and years and I’m getting my nutrition on too!
One of my go to spots for friendly and fast service ..Great food !

A very small location for chain of thai spots. The amount of seating is tripled in the summer when their outdoor section is open, but during the winter there are only maybe 10 tables in the place, so maybe think about take away. Great thai staples and friendly staff, Penny's is a good basic thai restaurant.

Penny's Noodles is my absolute go to restaurant when I need a delicious yet quick meal. I have never been adventurous enough to veer away from my favorite - the pad thai. However, the crispy rolls are also a great option if you aren't that hungry. Nestled in a convenient location to Roscoe Village/Lakeview, Penny's Noodles is highly recommended by both myself and my boyfriend!
Very very yummy Thai food. I love the dry wonton soup, everything else is great as well.
Another regular lunch spot for me. I can't properly pronounce many of the dishes, but they're good and authentic. Friendly service too. Recently, I've been hooked on the Spicy Basil w/ Chicken.

been coming to Penny's for years. the bucktown location is great because they give quality portions of take out.  my all time favorite is the veggie bowl.  that's all i have ever ordered.  can't go wrong here.

Penny's noodles on Sheffield has great Thai food.  They have a large selection of Thai food and are always very quick with orders.  Very friendly employees that are quick to answer questions and take orders.  I would recommend this restaurant to anyone looking for something quick and inexpensive.
Penny's Noodles has excellant soup and potstickers.

This place is cute, clean and right by the Redline so easy to get to.  The food is wonderful especially for the price point.  I love the chicken satay as a fast appetizer but almost anything on the menu is good!  I stick to small plates and then order and entree to split - potstickers were amazing!

Penny's is a quick-service style Thai restaraunt, located just blocks from Wrigley Field.   I've been here dozens of times, and have never been disappointed.  I typically get a spicy noodle dish, and it's terrific.  This place is also BYOB.
Quick and cheap stir fried noodles right in Wicker Park. A large HD TV for those sports events you cant catch at home. Closed Mondays unfortunately.

This great find has authentic food for a cheap price.  You can't go wrong with any of the noodle dishes.  I enjoy the artwork on the walls that showcases local artists work for sale.  Also, the Lakeview and Northfield are BYOB.
Good food and prices, but too small of a location.
Yummy! Amazing food! Our server, Miki, was so friendly!
It's BYOB, very inexpensive, and great Thai food!
